The menu lists that during happy hour, all house wine is $6/glass. We asked our waiter if they had any house rosé and he responded yes, that they did have a house rosé. Great! We get our bill and they had charged us $13 for that glass of “house” wine. We spoke to the waiter and manager, and apparently that wine wasn’t included in the happy hour. This felt extremely deceptive: the menu states that all house wine is $6/glass during happy hour, and our waiter verbally confirmed that the wine we ordered was house wine. Yet they charged us more than double for that same glass! They took the price down to $10, but it still was almost double what we thought we’d be paying. A really unfortunate resolution to an otherwise extremely pleasant dinner—left us with uncertainty regarding a return visit.

Restaurants like Mazi remind DC how tough the food industry is in this city. To survive, something exceptional must be baked into your strategy. At Mazi, it’s not obvious what their game is. After happy hour here, I can’t find something that’s worthy of 5 stars. Here’s why:  1) Food: The happy hour menu is decent, but the food wasn’t exceptional. My honey feta was good at first, but after 3-4 bites, it was all a little too much. My friend ordered the meatballs and found them dry and lacking flavor.  2) Drinks: Overpriced and mediocre. My margarita was $8 on happy hour prices and watered down. Every other sip, I wasn’t sure if I was sipping water or alcohol. My friends were charged $13 for Baileys on the rocks (it should be $7-$9) and $12.50 for vodka and club soda. If it was the best in that city, maybe, but overpriced for meh drinks.  There were a few good points:  1) Space: It’s not gorgeous, but the space layout and design are not bad. It’s simple yet a little more elegant than the average restaurant.  2) Service: Our server was attentive, kind, and gave us her honest recommendations.  I will say we went at 4pm on a Wednesday for happy hour and we had the entire place to ourselves. We stayed 1.5 hours and no one else came in. Time will tell if they survive.
